reviews.review_text: - Not truncated exactly, but it does feel like a short show even though it isn't really. They didn't really pull anything out, and the jams aren't all that interesting either. Very standard and lackluster set.

bread crumb Friend of the Devil was a second set song only 4 times in the Brent era.  It was played in the second set with a certain frequency from '76 to '78 but pretty quickly became an exclusive first set song once Brent joined the band.  I always find it a little odd, post '75, in the second set where the jams seems to be more exploratory than Friend allows.

A really nice audience recording.
Short show? The dead were the third band that played that day. David Bromberg opened then McGuinn Clark and Hillman. I don’t think the dead played as long as a solo show but we had a blast.

Awww. First Show What a great first show. It was the day after Lowell George died so a little on the mellow side but so many good memories. It was around Brent's 12th show. I ended up seeing his 12th to the last show too so that was wild. Rating it a 3 to the overall 100's of shows that I ended up seeing. It was a bit mellow but it brought me back, again and again.
